- in terminal type nano and a name for your program and end with .sh


nano video_download.sh

- in shell file add bash command #!/bin/zsh then cd into where Python program is saved the type python3 (program name).py $1

#!/bin/zsh

cd /Users/mack/(add rest of directory here)

python3 (program name).py $1

- save file by hitting Ctrl+x, then y to save, hit enter to exit

- to run the file, in the terminal type

zsh video_download.sh
